From PICL account Subject Re cats and pregnancy In article Klaus Hofmann I heard that a certain disease toxoplasmosys is transmitted by cats which can harm the unborn Does anybody know about it Is it a problem to have a cat in the same apartment The disease you are talking about is It is a protozoan that lives and multiplies within In cats the protozoan multiplies in the intestinal cells and eggs are shed in the cat's The protozoa can cross the placenta to infect the The disease may be asymptomatic after the baby is born or it may be very Toxo may cause blindness and mental Having a cat in the same apartment should not be a problem however pregnant women should not scoop or change the cat's In addition whoever does empty the litterbox should thoroughly wash his her hands before handling anything else especially Information came from The Merck Manual I hope this information is helpful to Elisa